==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|pæþ|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|paþaz}} (compare West Frisian {{term|paad|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|pad|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Pfad|lang=de}}), from Scytho-Sarmatian (compare Avestan ''pɑntɑ'', gen. ''pɑθɑ'' 'way', Old Persian ''pɑthi-''), from {{proto|Indo-European|pent-}} (compare English {{term|find}}). More at [[find]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/pæθ/}}
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/pɑːθ/|/pæθ/}}
